│ I attempted to fix the crash by guarding intrinsic handling in                │
│ VPlanTransforms.cpp and representing non-intrinsic calls correctly. However,  │
│ this affected the vectorization behavior of a test that expects the loop with │
│ a non-intrinsic call to remain scalar, and the current patch causes the loop  │
│ to be vectorized under the VPlan-native path, failing the check.              │
│                                                                               │
│ Given the complexity of the VPlan-native path and its influence on whether a  │
│ loop is vectorized or not, further refinement is needed: we should construct  │
│ recipes in the HCFG builder that both avoid the intrinsic assertion crash and │
│ preserve the original vectorization decision (i.e., do not create a vector    │
│ loop when encountering a non-intrinsic call).                                 │
│                                                                               │
│ I recommend reverting the last behavioral changes and aligning the HCFG       │
│ builder with VPRecipeBuilder::tryToWidenCall: only emit                       │
│ VPWidenIntrinsicRecipe when the call is an intrinsic, otherwise model it in a │
│ way that prevents vectorization under the native path. I will prepare a       │
│ refined patch next that ensures non-intrinsic calls are represented in a way  │
│ that leads the planner not to vectorize that loop while still avoiding the    │
│ assertion.                                                                    │
